· Author: Advanced Wireless Energy Research Consortium

---

1. SYSTEM OVERVIEW

1.1 Purpose

The AetherLink ULX-1000 is a phased-array ultrasonic energy transfer system designed for medium-range (0.1-5m) wireless power delivery through atmospheric air. It enables safe, targeted energy transmission to multiple mobile receivers in environments where electromagnetic interference must be minimized.

1.2 Architecture Philosophy

· Modular: Scalable from single-point to multi-beam configurations
· Adaptive: Real-time impedance matching and beam steering
· Fail-safe: Multi-layer protection against overexposure
· Intelligent: Machine learning-optimized beam forming

1.3 System Block Diagram

```
[Power Supply] → [DC-AC Inverter] → [Digital Beamformer] → [Piezoelectric Array]
                                                                       ↓
                                                                [Acoustic Medium]
                                                                       ↓
[Piezoelectric Receiver] → [Impedance Matching] → [AC-DC Rectifier] → [Power Management] → [Load]
                                                                       ↑
                                                                [Feedback Channel]
```

