2. PERFORMANCE SPECIFICATIOINS

2.1 Core Performance Metrics

Parameter Specification Conditions/Notes
Operating Frequency 40 kHz - 1.2 MHz Programmable in 1 kHz steps
Transmission Distance 0.1 - 5.0 meters Optimal: 1-3m
Maximum Output Power 100 W (continuous) Per transmitter array
Peak Efficiency 68% ± 5% At 1m, 25°C, 50% RH, matched impedance
Beam Width (-3dB) 3° - 15° Configurable via beamforming
Beam Steering Range ±60° azimuth, ±45° elevation Electronic steering
Power Density at Receiver 10 mW/cm² - 1 W/cm² Safety-limited maximum
Start-up Time < 100 ms Cold start to full operation
Response Time < 10 ms For beam redirection

2.2 Multi-Node Performance

Parameter Value
Maximum Simultaneous Receivers 8 independent beams
Channel Switching Time < 2 ms
Inter-channel Isolation > 25 dB
Power Allocation Granularity 1% steps

2.3 Environmental Performance

Condition Performance Impact
Temperature (0-40°C) Efficiency variation < ±8%
Humidity (20-80% RH) Additional loss 0.1 dB/%RH
Air Pressure (70-106 kPa) Negligible effect
Air Movement (< 5 m/s) Beam deflection < 0.5°
Obstructions (Partial) Adaptive beam reformatting

