3. TRANSMITTER SPECIFICATIONS

3.1 Acoustic Transducer Array

Component Specification
Array Configuration 32×32 hexagonal close-packed
Element Type PMN-PT piezoelectric composite
Element Size 5 mm diameter
Resonant Frequency 250 kHz (primary), 750 kHz (harmonic)
Bandwidth (-6dB) 15% of center frequency
Acoustic Impedance 10 MRayl (matched to air via matching layer)
Maximum Vibration Velocity 0.5 m/s (for reliability)
Element Crosstalk < -35 dB

3.2 Driving Electronics

Parameter Specification
Driver Type Class-D switching amplifier with H-bridge
Supply Voltage 48 VDC ±10%
Maximum Output Voltage (pk-pk) 400 V
Maximum Current 5 A per driver IC
Switching Frequency 10× operating frequency (min)
Total Harmonic Distortion < 1.5% at full power
Efficiency (Electrical to Acoustic) 85% typical

3.3 Beamforming Processor

Component Specification
Processor FPGA + DSP dual architecture
Beamforming Algorithm Time-reversal with phase conjugation
Beam Update Rate 100 Hz minimum
Phase Resolution 12 bits (0.088° steps at 250 kHz)
Amplitude Control 8 bits (0.4% steps)
Calibration Memory Stores 256 beam profiles

3.4 Thermal Management

System Specification
Maximum Heat Dissipation 35 W continuous
Cooling Method Passive finned heatsink + thermoelectric
Operating Temperature 0°C to 85°C (ambient)
Thermal Protection Automatic power reduction at 70°C

---

4. RECEIVER SPECIFICATIONS

4.1 Acoustic Reception System

Parameter Specification
Receiver Type Piezoelectric MEMS array (4×4)
Material Aluminum Nitride (AlN) on silicon
Resonant Frequency Matched to transmitter (250 kHz)
Bandwidth 30% of center frequency
Receiving Area 4 cm² effective
Acoustic Sensitivity 1.2 mV/Pa (at resonance)
Directionality ±30° half-angle for >50% efficiency

4.2 Power Conversion Chain

Stage Specification
Impedance Matching Tunable L-network, Q=50
AC-DC Rectification Active diode bridge, 95% efficiency
Voltage Regulation Buck-boost, 92% efficiency
Output Voltage 3.3V, 5V, 12V programmable
Output Current Up to 2A at 5V
Ripple Noise < 50 mV pk-pk
Maximum Power Point Tracking Yes, with perturb & observe algorithm

4.3 Feedback Channel

Parameter Specification
Feedback Method Backscatter modulation at 2.4 GHz (ISM band)
Data Rate 100 kbps
Transmitted Parameters Received power, voltage, temperature, ID
Update Rate 10 Hz typical, 100 Hz maximum
Range Up to 10 meters
Power Consumption < 10 mW

