8. SAFETY & REGULATORY COMPLIANCE

8.1 Acoustic Safety

Parameter Limit Compliance
SPL (Sound Pressure Level) < 145 dB re 20μPa Occupational safety limit
ISPTA (Spatial Peak Temporal Avg) < 720 mW/cm² FDA diagnostic ultrasound limit
Mechanical Index (MI) < 1.9 Medical ultrasound standard
Thermal Index (TI) < 6.0 Medical ultrasound standard
Audible Noise < 40 dBA at 1m Below ambient office noise

8.2 Electromagnetic Compliance

Standard Applicable Part
FCC Part 15 Unintentional radiator emissions
EN 55032 Electromagnetic compatibility
EN 61000-4 Immunity to disturbances
IEC 60601 Medical equipment (if applicable)

8.3 Safety Certifications

Certification Status
UL 60950-1 IT Equipment Safety
IEC 62368-1 Audio/Video Equipment
CE Mark European compliance
RoHS 3 Hazardous substances

8.4 Hazard Mitigation

Risk Mitigation Strategy
Overexposure Real-time SPL monitoring with automatic shutdown
Beam Obstruction Multi-sensor presence detection
Thermal Overload Temperature sensors on all critical components
Electrical Fault Galvanic isolation, ground fault detection

