9. TESTING & VALIDATION

9.1 Factory Testing Protocol

Test Method Acceptance Criteria
Acoustic Field Mapping Hydrophone array in anechoic chamber Beam pattern within 5% of simulation
Efficiency Measurement Calorimetric + electrical measurement > 60% system efficiency at 1m
Beam Steering Test Automated goniometer with receiver ±0.5° pointing accuracy
Thermal Cycling -10°C to +60°C, 50 cycles No performance degradation
Vibration Test 3-axis random vibration, 1 hour No mechanical failure

9.2 Field Testing Requirements

Test Conditions Success Criteria
Range Test Indoor, various humidities > 50% efficiency at 3m
Multi-Node Test 4 simultaneous receivers Power allocation within 10% of setpoint
Obstruction Test Partial beam blockage Recovery within 100ms
Long-term Test 1000 hours continuous operation < 2% efficiency degradation

9.3 Calibration Equipment Required

Equipment Specification Purpose
Reference Hydrophone 1-5 MHz, ±1.5 dB Acoustic pressure measurement
Laser Vibrometer 0-10 MHz, 1 pm resolution Transducer vibration measurement
Anechoic Chamber > 20 dB absorption at 40 kHz Isolation from reflections
Vector Network Analyzer 10 Hz - 300 MHz Impedance matching optimization
Thermal Camera 0.1°C resolution Hot spot detection

