11. DEPLOYMENT CONSIDERATIONS

11.1 Site Requirements

Requirement Specification
Space Requirements 0.5m clearance around transmitter
Mounting Surface Stable, vibration-isolated
Acoustic Environment Avoid highly reflective surfaces near beam path
Temperature Gradient < 2°C/m variation in beam path
Air Quality Minimal dust, smoke, or mist in beam path

11.2 Integration Guidelines

Consideration Recommendation
Multiple System Coordination Frequency hopping or time division
Receiver Placement Maintain line-of-sight with 30° angular margin
Interference Mitigation 1m separation from vibrating machinery
Power Infrastructure Dedicated circuit for each transmitter array
Network Integration VLAN separation for control traffic

11.3 Performance Optimization Tips

1. Humidity Control: Maintain 40-60% RH for optimal transmission
2. Temperature Stability: Allow 15-minute warm-up for stable operation
3. Calibration: Perform field calibration with receiver in actual position
4. Maintenance: Quarterly inspection of transducer surfaces for contamination
5. Monitoring: Implement continuous efficiency tracking with alert thresholds

