12. FUTURE DEVELOPMENT ROADMAP

12.1 Near-term (12-18 months)

· Higher Frequency Operation: Extend to 2.5 MHz for smaller beam width
· Improved Materials: Single crystal PMN-PT for 20% higher efficiency
· AI Optimization: Neural network-based beam prediction
· Miniaturization: 50% reduction in transmitter volume

12.2 Medium-term (2-3 years)

· Metamaterial Lenses: Acoustic metamaterials for beam shaping
· Quantum-enhanced Receivers: Piezoelectric devices with quantum dots
· Bi-directional Systems: Simultaneous power and high-speed data
· Self-calibrating Arrays: Automatic calibration via built-in sensors

12.3 Long-term (5+ years)

· Holographic Beamforming: Volumetric energy distribution
· Non-line-of-sight Operation: Acoustic waveguides and reflections
· Medical Integration: FDA-cleared for implant powering
· Space Applications: Lunar/Martian dust environment operation

